Happy Sunday! I would like to take the chance to welcome some new followers to my account by re-introducing myself. 🤍⁠
⁠
I was born and raised in Perth, Australia, however, I have been living in Los Angeles for 22 years. I’ve been fortunate enough to have lived and traveled all over the world which is another passion. I am married to the love of my life and most wonderful husband who works to make the world a better place through @worldtree.eco⁠
⁠
Most of you know me as the CEO and founder of @aea_interiors, a boutique residential design firm based in LA. Our team has grown a lot and we are excited to tell you that we are now moved in to our brand new office in Larchmont Village! ⁠After a 10 month remodel, it’s stunning! Summer party plans are in the works so look for an invite! 🤩
⁠
My passion for design has developed through 25 years of experience working with my team and partners on dozens of amazing projects which we are so, so proud of.. and guess what, it's just the beginning! There is much more to come and I'm excited to have you follow along on this journey! ⁠

How to choose the right color palette for your space! 👇🏻

✨ Consider the mood and atmosphere: Think about the mood you want to create in the space. Do you want it to be cozy and intimate, or bright and energetic? Different color palettes can evoke different emotions, so select colors that align with the desired ambiance.

✨ Start with a focal point: Choose a key element in the room that will serve as a focal point, such as a piece of furniture, artwork, or a statement rug. Draw inspiration from its colors and use them as a starting point to build your palette.

✨ Create balance: A well-balanced color palette typically includes a mix of dominant colors, secondary colors, and accent colors. The dominant color should cover the majority of the space, secondary colors can complement and support the dominant color, while accent colors add pops of interest and visual variety.

Always remember, when choosing a color palette, it’s a personal decision, and there are no strict rules. Trust your instincts and select colors that resonate with your style and the desired mood of the space. Press SAVE for later!

Don't be afraid to take the road less traveled. Take a walk on the wild side for a little bit, and explore your world beyond the path seemingly laid out for you.⁠
⁠
I also know it is often easier said than done. But in the years since leaving my home in Australia, taking whatever opportunities came my way, exploring the world, and eventually going after my dream job and my dream career, I can personally attest to how a world of possibilities opens up with every step you take outside of what was laid out in front of you and outside your comfort zone! Growth lies just outside of comfort. Take responsibility for your life. Be bold and live your life with your heart out front.

Pour your heart into what brings you joy, and have absolute faith in the process. Never take no for an answer, be persistent and know that failure is not failing, but indeed our best teacher. Pick yourself up and dust yourself off when you fall down! “Be” a great listener, (listen more than you talk). “Be” a true team player and leave your ego at home and stay humble. It’s all about coming together, working side by side to create something truly beautiful for all those involved. Enjoy the journey and the destination ✨ We all have a unique opportunity to spread our individual magic in the world. How great is it that life thought it needed you too? What a gift.
